## ex2

Example: n=1502

First print "Input an integer: "(note that there is a space after ':')

after getting the integer

print": "(note that there is a space after ':')

and turn flag to 1 (meaning not having outputted any number)

n is greater than 1000 so first check the part of 1502/1000 (aka 1) (part A) and the 1502%1000(aka 502)(part B).

For part A, 1 < 1000 , 1 < 100 ,1 < 20 ,1<10 and 1>=1

so print "one" and return.

turn flag to 0.

print" thousand"

For part B, 502<1000 ,502>=100

so print "five hundred and" then check 502%100(aka 2)

2<20 ,2<10 and 2>=1

so print "two"

return.

