b)
for m/n first let m+n=2

so m=n=1;

then let m+n=3

and start from m=1

then m=2

then m+n=4

start from n=1,then n=2 ,n=3 ...

so for m+n is even, start from n=1

for m+n is odd, start from m=1

c)

input: n
output: a/b

i<-1
while (n>i)
{
    n<-(n-i)
    i<-(i+1)
}
if (i%2==0) 
{
    b<-(i+1-n)
    a<-n
}
else 
{
    a<-(i+1-n)
    b<-n
}
return a,b
